The paper discusses differential privacy in the context of data analysis, specifically for histogram and synthetic data publishing. This topic falls under the sub-category of databases (cs.DB) as well as security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also discusses statistical techniques for improving accuracy, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and data structures for processing data, which falls under the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses information theory and its application to privacy, which falls under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT).
